          <div class="heading">API Overview</div>
          <p>The DistroPayment API uses API keys to authenticate requests. You can view and manage your API keys in the DestroPyment Dashboard
          DistroPayment provides HTTP based API which follows the essence of REST*. The HTTP protocol's rules are
            followed thereby enabling simple HTTP client tools like "curl" to be used.</p>
          <p class="heading_2">Here we are introducing a new way of handling payment securely and easily with DistroPayment API.</p>
          <div>You can use it in an easy way</div>

          <div id="ruby_section">
          <div class="heading pt-3">Errors</div>
          <p>Stripe uses conventional HTTP response codes to indicate the success or failure of an API request.
           In general: Codes in the 2xx range indicate success. Codes in the 4xx range indicate an error that failed given the information provided
          </p>
            <div class="init_code"><span class="color_0">
              <div class="code_api">
                  <h4> Summery of errors </h4>

                <div class="pl-3 mt-2">
                 <p> <span>200 - </span>OK	Everything worked as expected.<br>
                  <span>401 - </span>Unable to retrieve auth token! please check your keys.<br>
                  <span>401 - </span>Access token not found check it.<br></p>
                <h5> Argument of errors </h5>

               <p> Missing required parameter :  perameter name.</p>
               <p> Invalid Email: givin email.</p>
               <p> Invalid Amount : given amount</p>
               <p>Invalid Card number : given card_number </p>
               <p> Invalid Date : given date</p>
               <p> Invalid CVC  : given cvc</p>
               <p> Invalid month  : given month </p>
               <p> Invalid year  : given year</p>
               <p> </p>
               <p> </p>


                </div>
