           <div class="heading pt-3">Account setup</div>
            <p>Sign Up configure your site and your API keys. It is a global
              configuration and can set up as part of your server initialization.
              Your API keys carry many privileges, so be sure to keep them secure!
             Do not share your secret API keys in publicly accessible areas such as GitHub,
             client-side code, and so forth. </p>
           <div class="heading pt-3">Authentication token</div>
            <p>The first step is to create a token by sending API keys by a server-to-server POST request to DistroPayment.
            <br> Use the <span>https://distropayment.com/api/v1/auth_token/token</span></p>
            <div class="init_code"><span class="color_0">
              <div class="code_api">
                <div class="pl-3">
                  <pre  class="color_three">   <span>"client_secret":</span>"SE7fceb1d113129da5f35c498b8a0a7"</pre>
                  <pre  class="color_three">    <span>"client_public":</span>"IDa971f36df184f0ce0887cd55"</pre>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p><br>The response is in JSON format. A successful response provides the token in the location body, as follows:</p>
            <div class="init_code"><span class="color_three">{ <br>
            <pre  class="color_three"> <span> "access_token": </span> "2de7cbce1a775c2548835eb97b8a.."</pre>}</span></div>
           <div class="heading  pt-3">Virtual terminal</div>

            <p>Virtual terminal captures the shopper's sensitive card data via our Hosted Payment Fields, and binds it to the token.
             Your PCI compliance is reduced to SAQ-A because sensitive data never hits your sever.
            The second step is send token and card information server-to-server by POST request to Virtual terminal <br></p>
           <h6> <span class="m-2"> access_token  <span class="text-danger"> - required </span></span></h6>
           <p>Authentication token we have learn in privious section how to genrate, for successful sale transection access_token required  </p>

           <h6> <span class="m-2"> name  <span class="text-danger"> - required </span></span></h6>
           <p> Customer name is required to complete the transection </p>

           <h6> <span class="m-2"> email  <span class="text-danger"> - required </span></span></h6>
           <p> User's Email Address is required to complete the transection </p>

           <h6> <span class="m-2"> amount  <span class="text-danger"> - required </span></span></h6>

            <p> Amount intended to be collected by this payment.
             A positive integer representing how much to charge in the smallest currency unit $1 US.
             The minimum amount is $1 US or equivalent in charge currency.
             The amount value supports up to eight digits (e.g., a value of $99999999 US). </p>

           <h6> <span class="m-2"> card_number  <span class="text-danger"> - required </span></span></h6>
           <p> A valid card number is required to verify the source and complete the transection </p>

           <h6> <span class="m-2"> exp_date <span class="text-danger"> - required </span></span></h6>
           <p> To complete the transection the valid future date is must.  </p>

           <h6> <span class="m-2"> cvc<span class="text-danger"> - required </span></span></h6>
           <p> Card Verification Code  is also required</p>

          <h6> <span class="m-2"> phone <span class="text-secondary"> - optional </span></span></h6>
           <p>Phone Number is optional </p>

          <h6> <span class="m-2"> street_address <span class="text-secondary"> - optional </span></span></h6>
           <p> </p>

          <h6> <span class="m-2"> city <span class="text-secondary"> - optional </span></span></h6>
           <p> </p>
          <h6> <span class="m-2">country  <span class="text-secondary"> - optional </span></span></h6>
           <p> </p>
          <h6> <span class="m-2">zip_code  <span class="text-secondary"> - optional </span></span></h6>
           <p> </p>


            <p> Use the <span>https://distropayment.com/api/v1/sales/virtual_terminal </p>

